description.narrative: In 2021, the focus of the programme was on the two polio endemic countries, Afghanistan and Pakistan, and countries experiencing outbreaks of circulating vaccine derived polio virus (cVDPV). Wild Polio Virus cases reduced to 5 and cVDPVs to 601. Seven polio outbreaks were closed. During the past two years, there has been;a significant rise in type 2 cVPDV cases, mainly due to low population immunity levels, exacerbated by COVID-19. Contributing factors included sub-optimal routine immunization, low-quality immunization campaigns, delays in detection and response, as well as consistent access challenges, including insecurity and vaccine hesitancy due to misinformation and mobile populations. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:31/03/2022
